This package handles the processing of AIS packets received from the ais transponder.

    An IntentService subclass for handling asynchronous task requests in a service on a separate handler thread.
    AISMessageReceiver
    It runs on a separate thread.
    AIVDM
    This class is called from AISDecodingService to segregate the ASCII packet on the basis of comma.
    PostnReportClassA
    Class to process Type 1, 2 and 3 messages of class A transponders which shares a common reporting structure for navigational information; In normal operation, an AIS transceiver will broadcast a position report (type 1, 2, or 3) every 2 to 10 seconds depending on the vessel’s speed while underway, and every 3 minutes while the vessel is at anchor and stationary.
    PostnReportClassB
    Class to process Type 18 messages for vessels using Class B transmitters In normal operation, an AIS transceiver will broadcast a position report (type 1, 2, or 3) every 2 to 10 seconds depending on the vessel’s speed while underway, and every 3 minutes while the vessel is at anchor and stationary.
    StaticDataReport
    Class to process Type 24 messages.
    StaticVoyageData
    Class to process Type 5 messages of Class B transponders.

Package de.awi.floenavigation.aismessages Description

This package handles the processing of AIS packets received from the ais transponder.

AISMessageReceiver - It is a thread enabled from NetworkMonitor which establishes telnet connection between the tablet and the ais transponder. It also segragates packets based on AIVDM and AIVDO messages and forwards it to AISDecodingService AISDecodingService - It decodes the AIS packets and based on the packet type sends to the respective functions for further decoding. It receives the decoded values from the position report and static data classes and stores in the corresponding database tables. AIVDM - splits the AIS packet on the basis of comma and sends only the payloads to PostnReportClassA/ PostnReportClassB/StaticDataReport/StaticVoyageData. PostnReportClassA - Decoding of packets from class A transponders. PostnReportClassB - Decoding of packets from class B transponders. StaticDataReport - Decoding of static data packets from class B transponders StaticVoyageData - Decoding of static data packets from class A transponders
